<h2 id="when-to-use-buttons">When to use buttons</h2>

<p>Buttons should be used to help users carry out a task, like starting an application.</p>

<p>Buttons should be used to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Start a form</li>
  <li>Continue to the next question of a form</li>
  <li>Subscribe to something, such as email notifications</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="when-not-to-use-buttons">When not to use buttons</h2>

<p>Buttons shouldnâ€™t be used to replace links within the body of a page.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-use-buttons">How to use buttons</h2>

<p>Button text should be written in sentence case and clearly tell the user what the action is. For example, â€˜Start nowâ€™, â€˜Continueâ€™, â€˜Subscribeâ€™.</p>

<p>Having mulitple buttons on a page can confuse a user. GOV.UK recommends having one thing per page.</p>

